19/04/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- The army announced on Sunday (April 18th) that Turkish commandos have captured 13 pirates in the Indian Ocean.
Two skiffs and other property were seized in the operation.
A Turkish frigate is patrolling the area, including Somalia, as part of an international anti-piracy force.
(Press TV - 19/04/10;
AP - 18/04/10)
